{
  "doc_id": "10933",
  "text": "The partial loss of 5S and 45S rDNA repeats in Atropa represents an example of genomic diploidization, a wellknown phenomenon occurring during the evolution of polyploid organisms. This phenomenon embraces numerous functional and structural changes at different levels like loss of redundant gene expression, rearrangements of repeated genomic sequences, loss of chromosomes, etc. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
